Topic 2: String Operations ⭐⭐⭐

Today, we'll learn the most important string operations that are used in Python programming and DSA interviews.

These operations are the building blocks for almost every string problem.

1. What are String Operations?

String Operations are actions we perform on strings, such as:

Accessing characters
Slicing
Concatenation
Repetition
Searching
Comparison
Converting case
Replacing text
Splitting and joining

These operations are used in almost every interview question related to strings.

2. Accessing Characters (Indexing)

Every character has an index.

String = "Python"

Character :  P   y   t   h   o   n
Index     :  0   1   2   3   4   5
Negative  : -6  -5  -4  -3  -2  -1